title_full:

label: BLACK TRUFFLE
description:
Alvin Curran’s quietly joyful, spiritually enhancing, escapist 1975 masterpiece gets a new lease of life on Oren Ambarchi’s Black Truffle, heralding its wondrous mix of naif yet forward-looking experiments for new ears - trust there’s nowt quite like it!

Arriving from a seriously fecund creative patch, Eiko unfurls two gorgeous longform tapestries of thizzing drone, jazz drums, sax, field recordings and sustained ambient dream-pop vox finely chiselled into languorous chamber... more
